{"thig2.10":{"thig2.10:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 2.10 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 2.10 ","html":"<article id='thig2.10'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig2.10:0.2":{"pli":"Dukanipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Twos ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig2.10:0.3":{"pli":"Sāmātherīgāthā ","eng":"Sāmā ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig2.10:1.1":{"pli":"“Catukkhattuṃ pañcakkhattuṃ, ","eng":"Four or five times ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.10:1.2":{"pli":"vihārā upanikkhamiṃ; ","eng":"I left my dwelling. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.10:1.3":{"pli":"Aladdhā cetaso santiṃ, ","eng":"I had failed to find peace of heart, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.10:1.4":{"pli":"citte avasavattinī; ","eng":"or any control over my mind. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.10:1.5":{"pli":"Tassā me aṭṭhamī ratti, ","eng":"Now it is the eighth night ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.10:1.6":{"pli":"yato taṇhā samūhatā. ","eng":"since craving was eradicated. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig2.10:2.1":{"pli":"Bahūhi dukkhadhammehi, ","eng":"Though subject to so many painful things, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.10:2.2":{"pli":"appamādaratāya me; ","eng":"I have, through my love of diligence, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.10:2.3":{"pli":"Taṇhakkhayo anuppatto, ","eng":"reached the ending of craving, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.10:2.4":{"pli":"kataṃ buddhassa sāsanan”ti. ","eng":"and fulfilled the Buddha’s instructions. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig2.10:3.1":{"pli":"… Sāmā therī …. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p>"},"thig2.10:4.1":{"pli":"Dukanipāto niṭṭhito. ","html":"<p class='endbook'>{}</p></article>"}},"thig2.2":{"thig2.2:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 2.2 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 2.2 ","html":"<article id='thig2.2'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig2.2:0.2":{"pli":"Dukanipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Twos ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig2.2:0.3":{"pli":"Jentātherīgāthā ","eng":"Jentā ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig2.2:1.1":{"pli":"“Ye ime satta bojjhaṅgā, ","eng":"Of the seven awakening factors, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.2:1.2":{"pli":"maggā nibbānapattiyā; ","eng":"the path for attaining extinguishment, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.2:1.3":{"pli":"Bhāvitā te mayā sabbe, ","eng":"I have developed them all, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.2:1.4":{"pli":"yathā buddhena desitā. ","eng":"just as the Buddha taught. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig2.2:2.1":{"pli":"Diṭṭho hi me so bhagavā, ","eng":"For I have seen the Blessed One, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.2:2.2":{"pli":"antimoyaṃ samussayo; ","eng":"and this bag of bones is my last. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.2:2.3":{"pli":"Vikkhīṇo jātisaṃsāro, ","eng":"Transmigration through births is finished, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.2:2.4":{"pli":"natthi dāni punabbhavo”ti. ","eng":"now there’ll be no more future lives. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig2.2:3.1":{"pli":"Itthaṃ sudaṃ jentā therī gāthāyo abhāsitthāti. ","eng":"That is how these verses were recited by the senior nun Jentā. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"thig2.3":{"thig2.3:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 2.3 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 2.3 ","html":"<article id='thig2.3'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig2.3:0.2":{"pli":"Dukanipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Twos ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig2.3:0.3":{"pli":"Sumaṅgalamātātherīgāthā ","eng":"Sumaṅgala’s Mother ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig2.3:1.1":{"pli":"“Sumuttikā sumuttikā, ","eng":"I’m well freed, well freed, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"This verse, like <a href='index.html?q=thig1.11'>Thig 1.11</a>, hinges on double entendres of kitchen drudgery and sex, and hence is playfully ambiguous. It is a Buddhist counterpart to Rig Veda 1.28, which parallels the act of sex with the pounding of mortar and pestle, situating the ritual in the kitchen. | The nun here is presumably the mother of the Sumaṅgala at <a href='index.html?q=thag1.43'>Thag 1.43</a>, whose verses are similar. "},"thig2.3:1.2":{"pli":"Sādhumuttikāmhi musalassa; ","eng":"so very well freed from the pestle! ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"The pestle (<i lang='pi' translate='no'>musala</i>)  is the male, routinely paired with the female mortar (Śathapatha Brāhmaṇa 7.5.1.38). "},"thig2.3:1.3":{"pli":"Ahiriko me chattakaṃ vāpi, ","eng":"My shameless husband was most certainly a mushroom, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"The mortar was sixteen inches of rock hard wood (ŚB 1.1.4.7 and Eggeling’s note). I don’t think calling it a mushroom is meant as a compliment. On the other hand, if <i lang='pi' translate='no'>vāpi</i> (“most certainly”) is emended to <i lang='pi' translate='no'>vāti</i> (or <i lang='pi' translate='no'>vāyi</i>), it is the wind that causes erections (<a href='index.html?q=pli-tv-bu-vb-pj1#10.17.6'>Bu Pj 1:10.17.6</a>, cf. RV 1.28.6), “my husband inflated like a mushroom” (which pops up out of nowhere). "},"thig2.3:1.4":{"pli":"Ukkhalikā me deḍḍubhaṃ vāti. ","eng":"my mortar wafted like an eel. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>","comm":"I prefer “mortar” for <i lang='pi' translate='no'>ukkhalikā</i> as the complement of “pestle”. Compare Sanskrit <i lang='pi' translate='no'>ulūkhala</i> (or <i lang='pi' translate='no'>ulūkhalaka</i>) throughout RV 1.28, and also ŚB 7.5.1.22, “the mortar is the womb of all breaths”. If the sense “little cauldron” is preferred, see ŚB 6.6.2.8, “the cauldron is female, the fire male” (also ŚB 7.1.1.42). The two terms are used in the same passage in this sense at ŚB 7.5.1.26. | <i lang='pi' translate='no'>Deḍḍubha</i> is a “water-snake” or eel (<a href='index.html?q=pli-tv-kd15#29.2.2'>Kd 15:29.2.2</a>). But it is also a spelling of “drum”, in which case we might emend <i lang='pi' translate='no'>vāti</i> to <i lang='pi' translate='no'>vādi</i>, yielding “my mortar was drum-sounding”, as the mortar “sounds” when pounded like the “drum of victors” (RV 1.28.5). | For <i lang='pi' translate='no'>vāti</i> in the sense, “waft an odor”, see <a href='index.html?q=vv38#6.3'>Vv 38:6.3</a>. "},"thig2.3:2.1":{"pli":"Rāgañca ahaṃ dosañca, ","eng":"Greed and hate sizzle and hiss ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.3:2.2":{"pli":"Cicciṭi cicciṭīti vihanāmi; ","eng":"as I squelch them. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.3:2.3":{"pli":"Sā rukkhamūlamupagamma, ","eng":"Having gone to the root of a tree, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.3:2.4":{"pli":"Aho sukhanti sukhato jhāyāmī”ti. ","eng":"I meditate happily, thinking, “Oh, what bliss!” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig2.3:3.1":{"pli":"… Sumaṅgalamātā therī …. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"thig2.4":{"thig2.4:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 2.4 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 2.4 ","html":"<article id='thig2.4'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig2.4:0.2":{"pli":"Dukanipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Twos ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig2.4:0.3":{"pli":"Aḍḍhakāsitherīgāthā ","eng":"Aḍḍhakāsi ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig2.4:1.1":{"pli":"“Yāva kāsijanapado, ","eng":"The price for my services ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.4:1.2":{"pli":"suṅko me tatthako ahu; ","eng":"amounted to the nation of Kāsi. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.4:1.3":{"pli":"Taṃ katvā negamo agghaṃ, ","eng":"By setting that price, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.4:1.4":{"pli":"aḍḍhenagghaṃ ṭhapesi maṃ. ","eng":"the townsfolk made me priceless. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig2.4:2.1":{"pli":"Atha nibbindahaṃ rūpe, ","eng":"Then, growing disillusioned with my form, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.4:2.2":{"pli":"nibbindañca virajjahaṃ; ","eng":"I became dispassionate. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.4:2.3":{"pli":"Mā puna jātisaṃsāraṃ, ","eng":"Don’t journey on and on, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.4:2.4":{"pli":"sandhāveyyaṃ punappunaṃ; ","eng":"transmigrating through rebirths! ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.4:2.5":{"pli":"Tisso vijjā sacchikatā, ","eng":"I’ve realized the three knowledges, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.4:2.6":{"pli":"kataṃ buddhassa sāsanan”ti. ","eng":"and fulfilled the Buddha’s instructions. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig2.4:3.1":{"pli":"… Aḍḍhakāsi therī …. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"thig2.5":{"thig2.5:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 2.5 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 2.5 ","html":"<article id='thig2.5'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig2.5:0.2":{"pli":"Dukanipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Twos ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig2.5:0.3":{"pli":"Cittātherīgāthā ","eng":"Cittā ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig2.5:1.1":{"pli":"“Kiñcāpi khomhi kisikā, ","eng":"Even though I’m skinny, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.5:1.2":{"pli":"gilānā bāḷhadubbalā; ","eng":"sick, and very feeble, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.5:1.3":{"pli":"Daṇḍamolubbha gacchāmi, ","eng":"I climb the mountain, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.5:1.4":{"pli":"pabbataṃ abhirūhiya. ","eng":"leaning on a staff. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig2.5:2.1":{"pli":"Saṅghāṭiṃ nikkhipitvāna, ","eng":"Having laid down my outer robe, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.5:2.2":{"pli":"pattakañca nikujjiya; ","eng":"and overturned my bowl, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.5:2.3":{"pli":"Sele khambhesimattānaṃ, ","eng":"propping myself against a rock, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.5:2.4":{"pli":"tamokhandhaṃ padāliyā”ti. ","eng":"I shattered the mass of darkness. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig2.5:3.1":{"pli":"… Cittā therī …. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"thig2.6":{"thig2.6:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 2.6 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 2.6 ","html":"<article id='thig2.6'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig2.6:0.2":{"pli":"Dukanipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Twos ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig2.6:0.3":{"pli":"Mettikātherīgāthā ","eng":"Mettikā ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig2.6:1.1":{"pli":"“Kiñcāpi khomhi dukkhitā, ","eng":"Though in pain, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.6:1.2":{"pli":"dubbalā gatayobbanā; ","eng":"feeble, my youth long gone, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.6:1.3":{"pli":"Daṇḍamolubbha gacchāmi, ","eng":"I climb the mountain, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.6:1.4":{"pli":"pabbataṃ abhirūhiya. ","eng":"leaning on a staff. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig2.6:2.1":{"pli":"Nikkhipitvāna saṅghāṭiṃ, ","eng":"Having laid down my outer robe ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.6:2.2":{"pli":"pattakañca nikujjiya; ","eng":"and overturned my bowl, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.6:2.3":{"pli":"Nisinnā camhi selamhi, ","eng":"sitting on a rock, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.6:2.4":{"pli":"atha cittaṃ vimucci me; ","eng":"my mind was freed. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.6:2.5":{"pli":"Tisso vijjā anuppattā, ","eng":"I’ve attained the three knowledges, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.6:2.6":{"pli":"kataṃ buddhassa sāsanan”ti. ","eng":"and fulfilled the Buddha’s instructions. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig2.6:3.1":{"pli":"… Mettikā therī …. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"thig2.7":{"thig2.7:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 2.7 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 2.7 ","html":"<article id='thig2.7'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig2.7:0.2":{"pli":"Dukanipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Twos ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig2.7:0.3":{"pli":"Mittātherīgāthā ","eng":"Mittā (2nd) ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig2.7:1.1":{"pli":"“Cātuddasiṃ pañcadasiṃ, ","eng":"I rejoiced in the host of gods, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.7:1.2":{"pli":"yā ca pakkhassa aṭṭhamī; ","eng":"having observed the sabbath ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.7:1.3":{"pli":"Pāṭihāriyapakkhañca, ","eng":"complete in all eight factors, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.7:1.4":{"pli":"aṭṭhaṅgasusamāgataṃ. ","eng":"on the fourteenth and the fifteenth days, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig2.7:2.1":{"pli":"Uposathaṃ upāgacchiṃ, ","eng":"and the eighth day of the fortnight, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.7:2.2":{"pli":"devakāyābhinandinī; ","eng":"as well as on the fortnightly special displays. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.7:2.3":{"pli":"Sājja ekena bhattena, ","eng":"Today I eat just once a day, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.7:2.4":{"pli":"muṇḍā saṅghāṭipārutā; ","eng":"my head is shaven, I wear the outer robe. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.7:2.5":{"pli":"Devakāyaṃ na patthehaṃ, ","eng":"I don’t long for the host of gods, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.7:2.6":{"pli":"vineyya hadaye daran”ti. ","eng":"for stress has been removed from my heart. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig2.7:3.1":{"pli":"… Mittā therī …. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"thig2.8":{"thig2.8:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 2.8 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 2.8 ","html":"<article id='thig2.8'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig2.8:0.2":{"pli":"Dukanipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Twos ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig2.8:0.3":{"pli":"Abhayamātutherīgāthā ","eng":"To Abhayā’s Mother From Her Daughter ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig2.8:1.1":{"pli":"“Uddhaṃ pādatalā amma, ","eng":"My dear mother, examine this body, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"Authorship is unclear in these verses. The first verse is addressed to the mother. The commentary says it was by her son Abhaya, but I think it is more likely by her daughter Abhayā who features in the next poem. "},"thig2.8:1.2":{"pli":"adho ve kesamatthakā; ","eng":"up from the soles of the feet, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.8:1.3":{"pli":"Paccavekkhassumaṃ kāyaṃ, ","eng":"and down from the tips of the hairs, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.8:1.4":{"pli":"asuciṃ pūtigandhikaṃ. ","eng":"so impure and foul-smelling. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig2.8:2.1":{"pli":"Evaṃ viharamānāya, ","eng":"Meditating like this, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"The feminine declension of the last words show that this verse is spoken by a woman. The commentary says it was by the mother, who has quoted her son’s words and adds her own. I read both verses as spoken by the daughter. "},"thig2.8:2.2":{"pli":"sabbo rāgo samūhato; ","eng":"all my lust is eradicated. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.8:2.3":{"pli":"Pariḷāho samucchinno, ","eng":"The fever of passion is cut off, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.8:2.4":{"pli":"sītibhūtāmhi nibbutā”ti. ","eng":"I’m cooled and quenched. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>","comm":"It is only from the feminine declension of the last words that we can be sure it is the daughter Abhayā speaking. "},"thig2.8:3.1":{"pli":"… Abhayamātā therī …. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"thig2.9":{"thig2.9:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 2.9 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 2.9 ","html":"<article id='thig2.9'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig2.9:0.2":{"pli":"Dukanipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Twos ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig2.9:0.3":{"pli":"Abhayātherīgāthā ","eng":"Abhayā ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig2.9:1.1":{"pli":"“Abhaye bhiduro kāyo, ","eng":"Abhayā, the body is fragile, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"The commentary says that Abhayā is exhorting herself here. "},"thig2.9:1.2":{"pli":"yattha satā puthujjanā; ","eng":"yet ordinary people are attached to it. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.9:1.3":{"pli":"Nikkhipissāmimaṃ dehaṃ, ","eng":"I’ll lay down the body, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.9:1.4":{"pli":"sampajānā satīmatī. ","eng":"aware and mindful. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig2.9:2.1":{"pli":"Bahūhi dukkhadhammehi, ","eng":"Though subject to so many painful things, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.9:2.2":{"pli":"appamādaratāya me; ","eng":"I have, through my love of diligence, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.9:2.3":{"pli":"Taṇhakkhayo anuppatto, ","eng":"reached the ending of craving, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig2.9:2.4":{"pli":"kataṃ buddhassa sāsanan”ti. ","eng":"and fulfilled the Buddha’s instructions. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig2.9:3.1":{"pli":"… Abhayā therī …. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"thig3.1":{"thig3.1:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 3.1 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 3.1 ","html":"<article id='thig3.1'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig3.1:0.2":{"pli":"Tikanipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Threes ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig3.1:0.3":{"pli":"Aparāsāmātherīgāthā ","eng":"Another Sāmā ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig3.1:1.1":{"pli":"“Paṇṇavīsativassāni, ","eng":"In the twenty-five years ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.1:1.2":{"pli":"yato pabbajitāya me; ","eng":"since I went forth, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.1:1.3":{"pli":"Nābhijānāmi cittassa, ","eng":"I don’t know that I had ever found ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.1:1.4":{"pli":"samaṃ laddhaṃ kudācanaṃ. ","eng":"serenity in my mind. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig3.1:2.1":{"pli":"Aladdhā cetaso santiṃ, ","eng":"I had failed to find peace of heart, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.1:2.2":{"pli":"citte avasavattinī; ","eng":"or any control over my mind. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.1:2.3":{"pli":"Tato saṃvegamāpādiṃ, ","eng":"When I remembered the victor’s instructions, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.1:2.4":{"pli":"saritvā jinasāsanaṃ. ","eng":"I was struck with a sense of urgency. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig3.1:3.1":{"pli":"Bahūhi dukkhadhammehi, ","eng":"Though subject to so many painful things, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.1:3.2":{"pli":"appamādaratāya me; ","eng":"I have, through my love of diligence, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.1:3.3":{"pli":"Taṇhakkhayo anuppatto, ","eng":"reached the ending of craving, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.1:3.4":{"pli":"kataṃ buddhassa sāsanaṃ; ","eng":"and fulfilled the Buddha’s instructions. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.1:3.5":{"pli":"Ajja me sattamī ratti, ","eng":"This is the seventh day ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.1:3.6":{"pli":"yato taṇhā visositā”ti. ","eng":"since my craving dried up. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig3.1:4.1":{"pli":"… Aparā sāmā therī …. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"thig3.2":{"thig3.2:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 3.2 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 3.2 ","html":"<article id='thig3.2'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig3.2:0.2":{"pli":"Tikanipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Threes ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig3.2:0.3":{"pli":"Uttamātherīgāthā ","eng":"Uttamā ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig3.2:1.1":{"pli":"“Catukkhattuṃ pañcakkhattuṃ, ","eng":"Four or five times ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.2:1.2":{"pli":"vihārā upanikkhamiṃ; ","eng":"I left my dwelling. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.2:1.3":{"pli":"Aladdhā cetaso santiṃ, ","eng":"I had failed to find peace of heart, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.2:1.4":{"pli":"citte avasavattinī. ","eng":"or any control over my mind. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig3.2:2.1":{"pli":"Sā bhikkhuniṃ upagacchiṃ, ","eng":"I approached a nun ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.2:2.2":{"pli":"yā me saddhāyikā ahu; ","eng":"in whom I had faith. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.2:2.3":{"pli":"Sā me dhammamadesesi, ","eng":"She taught me the Dhamma: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.2:2.4":{"pli":"khandhāyatanadhātuyo. ","eng":"the aggregates, sense fields, and elements. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig3.2:3.1":{"pli":"Tassā dhammaṃ suṇitvāna, ","eng":"When I had heard her teaching, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.2:3.2":{"pli":"Yathā maṃ anusāsi sā; ","eng":"in accordance with her instructions, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.2:3.3":{"pli":"Sattāhaṃ ekapallaṅkena, ","eng":"I sat cross-legged for seven days without moving, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.2:3.4":{"pli":"Nisīdiṃ pītisukhasamappitā; ","eng":"given over to rapture and bliss. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.2:3.5":{"pli":"Aṭṭhamiyā pāde pasāresiṃ, ","eng":"On the eighth day I stretched out my feet, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.2:3.6":{"pli":"Tamokhandhaṃ padāliyā”ti. ","eng":"having shattered the mass of darkness. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig3.2:4.1":{"pli":"… Uttamā therī …. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"thig3.3":{"thig3.3:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 3.3 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 3.3 ","html":"<article id='thig3.3'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig3.3:0.2":{"pli":"Tikanipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Threes ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig3.3:0.3":{"pli":"Aparāuttamātherīgāthā ","eng":"Another Uttamā ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig3.3:1.1":{"pli":"“Ye ime satta bojjhaṅgā, ","eng":"Of the seven awakening factors, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.3:1.2":{"pli":"maggā nibbānapattiyā; ","eng":"the path for attaining extinguishment, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.3:1.3":{"pli":"Bhāvitā te mayā sabbe, ","eng":"I have developed them all, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.3:1.4":{"pli":"yathā buddhena desitā. ","eng":"just as the Buddha taught. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig3.3:2.1":{"pli":"Suññatassānimittassa, ","eng":"I attain the meditations on emptiness ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.3:2.2":{"pli":"lābhinīhaṃ yadicchakaṃ; ","eng":"and signlessness whenever I want. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.3:2.3":{"pli":"Orasā dhītā buddhassa, ","eng":"I am the Buddha’s rightful daughter, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.3:2.4":{"pli":"nibbānābhiratā sadā. ","eng":"always delighting in extinguishment. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig3.3:3.1":{"pli":"Sabbe kāmā samucchinnā, ","eng":"All sensual pleasures are cut off, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.3:3.2":{"pli":"ye dibbā ye ca mānusā; ","eng":"whether human or heavenly. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.3:3.3":{"pli":"Vikkhīṇo jātisaṃsāro, ","eng":"Transmigration through births is finished, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.3:3.4":{"pli":"natthi dāni punabbhavo”ti. ","eng":"now there’ll be no more future lives. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig3.3:4.1":{"pli":"… Aparā uttamā therī …. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"thig3.4":{"thig3.4:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 3.4 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 3.4 ","html":"<article id='thig3.4'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig3.4:0.2":{"pli":"Tikanipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Threes ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig3.4:0.3":{"pli":"Dantikātherīgāthā ","eng":"Dantikā ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig3.4:1.1":{"pli":"“Divāvihārā nikkhamma, ","eng":"Leaving my day’s meditation ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.4:1.2":{"pli":"gijjhakūṭamhi pabbate; ","eng":"on Vulture’s Peak Mountain, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.4:1.3":{"pli":"Nāgaṃ ogāhamuttiṇṇaṃ, ","eng":"I saw an elephant on the riverbank ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.4:1.4":{"pli":"nadītīramhi addasaṃ. ","eng":"having just come up from his bath. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig3.4:2.1":{"pli":"Puriso aṅkusamādāya, ","eng":"A man, taking a pole with a hook, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.4:2.2":{"pli":"‘dehi pādan’ti yācati; ","eng":"asked the elephant, “Give me your foot.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.4:2.3":{"pli":"Nāgo pasārayī pādaṃ, ","eng":"The elephant presented his foot, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.4:2.4":{"pli":"puriso nāgamāruhi. ","eng":"and the man mounted him. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig3.4:3.1":{"pli":"Disvā adantaṃ damitaṃ, ","eng":"Seeing a wild beast so tamed, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.4:3.2":{"pli":"manussānaṃ vasaṃ gataṃ; ","eng":"submitting to human control, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.4:3.3":{"pli":"Tato cittaṃ samādhesiṃ, ","eng":"my mind became serene: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.4:3.4":{"pli":"khalu tāya vanaṃ gatā”ti. ","eng":"<em>that</em> is why I’ve gone to the forest! ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig3.4:4.1":{"pli":"… Dantikā therī …. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"thig3.5":{"thig3.5:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 3.5 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 3.5 ","html":"<article id='thig3.5'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig3.5:0.2":{"pli":"Tikanipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Threes ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig3.5:0.3":{"pli":"Ubbiritherīgāthā ","eng":"Ubbirī ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig3.5:1.1":{"pli":"“Amma jīvāti vanamhi kandasi, ","eng":"“You cry ‘Live, my dear mother!’ in the forest. ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"In her distress, Ubbirī addresses her daughter as “mother”. The speaker of this verse, who is trying to help the distressed Ubbirī, is not named in the text, but the commentary identifies it as the Buddha. "},"thig3.5:1.2":{"pli":"Attānaṃ adhigaccha ubbiri; ","eng":"Ubbirī, get a hold of yourself! ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.5:1.3":{"pli":"Cullāsītisahassāni, ","eng":"Eighty-four thousand people, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.5:1.4":{"pli":"Sabbā jīvasanāmikā; ","eng":"all named ‘Live’, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.5:1.5":{"pli":"Etamhāḷāhane daḍḍhā, ","eng":"have been burnt in this funeral ground: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.5:1.6":{"pli":"Tāsaṃ kamanusocasi”. ","eng":"which one do you grieve for?” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig3.5:2.1":{"pli":"“Abbahī vata me sallaṃ, ","eng":"“Oh! For you have plucked the arrow from me, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.5:2.2":{"pli":"duddasaṃ hadayassitaṃ; ","eng":"so hard to see, stuck in the heart. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.5:2.3":{"pli":"Yaṃ me sokaparetāya, ","eng":"You’ve swept away the grief for my daughter ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.5:2.4":{"pli":"dhītusokaṃ byapānudi. ","eng":"in which I once was mired. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig3.5:3.1":{"pli":"Sājja abbūḷhasallāhaṃ, ","eng":"Today I’ve plucked the arrow, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.5:3.2":{"pli":"Nicchātā parinibbutā; ","eng":"I’m hungerless, quenched. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.5:3.3":{"pli":"Buddhaṃ dhammañca saṅghañca, ","eng":"I go for refuge to that sage, the Buddha, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.5:3.4":{"pli":"Upemi saraṇaṃ munin”ti. ","eng":"to his teaching, and to the Sangha.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig3.5:4.1":{"pli":"… Ubbirī therī …. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"thig3.6":{"thig3.6:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 3.6 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 3.6 ","html":"<article id='thig3.6'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig3.6:0.2":{"pli":"Tikanipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Threes ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig3.6:0.3":{"pli":"Sukkātherīgāthā ","eng":"Sukkā ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig3.6:1.1":{"pli":"“Kiṃme katā rājagahe manussā, ","eng":"“What’s up with these people in Rājagaha? ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.6:1.2":{"pli":"Madhuṃ pītāva acchare; ","eng":"They sprawl like they’ve been drinking mead! ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.6:1.3":{"pli":"Ye sukkaṃ na upāsanti, ","eng":"They don’t attend on Sukkā ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.6:1.4":{"pli":"Desentiṃ buddhasāsanaṃ. ","eng":"as she teaches the Buddha’s instructions. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig3.6:2.1":{"pli":"Tañca appaṭivānīyaṃ, ","eng":"But the wise—","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.6:2.2":{"pli":"asecanakamojavaṃ; ","eng":"it’s as if they drink it up, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.6:2.3":{"pli":"Pivanti maññe sappaññā, ","eng":"so irresistible, delectable, and nutritious, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.6:2.4":{"pli":"valāhakamivaddhagū. ","eng":"like travelers enjoying a cool cloud.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig3.6:3.1":{"pli":"Sukkā sukkehi dhammehi, ","eng":"“She’s known as Sukkā because of her bright qualities, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.6:3.2":{"pli":"vītarāgā samāhitā; ","eng":"free of greed, serene. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.6:3.3":{"pli":"Dhāreti antimaṃ dehaṃ, ","eng":"She bears her final body, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.6:3.4":{"pli":"jetvā māraṃ savāhinin”ti. ","eng":"having vanquished Māra with his legions.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig3.6:4.1":{"pli":"… Sukkā therī …. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"thig3.7":{"thig3.7:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 3.7 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 3.7 ","html":"<article id='thig3.7'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig3.7:0.2":{"pli":"Tikanipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Threes ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig3.7:0.3":{"pli":"Selātherīgāthā ","eng":"Selā ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig3.7:1.1":{"pli":"“Natthi nissaraṇaṃ loke, ","eng":"“There’s no escape in the world, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.7:1.2":{"pli":"kiṃ vivekena kāhasi; ","eng":"so what will seclusion do for you? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.7:1.3":{"pli":"Bhuñjāhi kāmaratiyo, ","eng":"Enjoy erotic delights; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.7:1.4":{"pli":"māhu pacchānutāpinī”. ","eng":"don’t regret it later.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig3.7:2.1":{"pli":"“Sattisūlūpamā kāmā, ","eng":"“Sensual pleasures are like swords and spears ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.7:2.2":{"pli":"khandhāsaṃ adhikuṭṭanā; ","eng":"the aggregates are their chopping block. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.7:2.3":{"pli":"Yaṃ tvaṃ ‘kāmaratiṃ’ brūsi, ","eng":"What you call erotic delight ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.7:2.4":{"pli":"‘aratī’ dāni sā mama. ","eng":"is now no delight for me. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig3.7:3.1":{"pli":"Sabbattha vihatā nandī, ","eng":"Relishing is banished in every respect, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.7:3.2":{"pli":"Tamokhandho padālito; ","eng":"and the mass of darkness is shattered. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.7:3.3":{"pli":"Evaṃ jānāhi pāpima, ","eng":"So know this, Wicked One: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.7:3.4":{"pli":"Nihato tvamasi antakā”ti. ","eng":"you’re beaten, terminator!” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig3.7:4.1":{"pli":"… Selā therī …. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"thig3.8":{"thig3.8:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 3.8 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 3.8 ","html":"<article id='thig3.8'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig3.8:0.2":{"pli":"Tikanipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Threes ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig3.8:0.3":{"pli":"Somātherīgāthā ","eng":"Somā ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig3.8:1.1":{"pli":"“Yaṃ taṃ isīhi pattabbaṃ, ","eng":"“That state’s very challenging; ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.8:1.2":{"pli":"ṭhānaṃ durabhisambhavaṃ; ","eng":"it’s for the sages to attain. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.8:1.3":{"pli":"Na taṃ dvaṅgulapaññāya, ","eng":"With her two-inch wisdom, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.8:1.4":{"pli":"sakkā pappotumitthiyā”. ","eng":"it’s not possible for a woman.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig3.8:2.1":{"pli":"“Itthibhāvo no kiṃ kayirā, ","eng":"“What difference does womanhood make ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.8:2.2":{"pli":"cittamhi susamāhite; ","eng":"when the mind is serene, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.8:2.3":{"pli":"Ñāṇamhi vattamānamhi, ","eng":"and knowledge is present ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.8:2.4":{"pli":"sammā dhammaṃ vipassato. ","eng":"as you rightly discern the Dhamma. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig3.8:3.1":{"pli":"Sabbattha vihatā nandī, ","eng":"Relishing is banished in every respect, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.8:3.2":{"pli":"Tamokhandho padālito; ","eng":"and the mass of darkness is shattered. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.8:3.3":{"pli":"Evaṃ jānāhi pāpima, ","eng":"So know this, Wicked One: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig3.8:3.4":{"pli":"Nihato tvamasi antakā”ti. ","eng":"you’re beaten, terminator!” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig3.8:4.1":{"pli":"… Somā therī …. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p>"},"thig3.8:5.1":{"pli":"Tikanipāto niṭṭhito. ","html":"<p class='endbook'>{}</p></article>"}},"thig4.1":{"thig4.1:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 4.1 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 4.1 ","html":"<article id='thig4.1'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig4.1:0.2":{"pli":"Catukkanipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Fours ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig4.1:0.3":{"pli":"Bhaddākāpilānītherīgāthā ","eng":"Bhaddā Daughter of Kapila ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig4.1:1.1":{"pli":"“Putto buddhassa dāyādo, ","eng":"Kassapa is the son and heir of the Buddha, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig4.1:1.2":{"pli":"kassapo susamāhito; ","eng":"whose mind is immersed in samādhi. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig4.1:1.3":{"pli":"Pubbenivāsaṃ yovedi, ","eng":"He who knows his past lives, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig4.1:1.4":{"pli":"saggāpāyañca passati. ","eng":"sees heaven and places of loss, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig4.1:2.1":{"pli":"Atho jātikkhayaṃ patto, ","eng":"and has attained the end of rebirth: ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig4.1:2.2":{"pli":"abhiññāvosito muni; ","eng":"is a sage of perfect insight. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig4.1:2.3":{"pli":"Etāhi tīhi vijjāhi, ","eng":"It’s because of these three knowledges ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig4.1:2.4":{"pli":"tevijjo hoti brāhmaṇo. ","eng":"that the brahmin is a master of the three knowledges. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig4.1:3.1":{"pli":"Tatheva bhaddā kāpilānī, ","eng":"In exactly the same way, Bhaddā daughter of Kapila ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig4.1:3.2":{"pli":"tevijjā maccuhāyinī; ","eng":"is master of the three knowledges, <j>conqueror of death. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"<i lang='pi' translate='no'>Maccuhāyi</i> is glossed by the commentaries as either “abandoner” (<i lang='pi' translate='no'>Maccuhāyinanti maraṇapariccāginaṁ</i>) or “conqueror” (<i lang='pi' translate='no'>maraṇābhibhū maccuhāyī</i>). The phrase seems to be used in martial contexts where it carries a similar force to <i lang='pi' translate='no'>jetvā māraṁ</i> just below. "},"thig4.1:3.3":{"pli":"Dhāreti antimaṃ dehaṃ, ","eng":"She bears her final body, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig4.1:3.4":{"pli":"jetvā māraṃ savāhiniṃ. ","eng":"having vanquished Māra with his legions. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig4.1:4.1":{"pli":"Disvā ādīnavaṃ loke, ","eng":"Seeing the danger of the world, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig4.1:4.2":{"pli":"ubho pabbajitā mayaṃ; ","eng":"both of us went forth. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig4.1:4.3":{"pli":"Tyamha khīṇāsavā dantā, ","eng":"Now we are tamed, our defilements have ended; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig4.1:4.4":{"pli":"sītibhūtamha nibbutā”ti. ","eng":"we’ve become cooled and quenched. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig4.1:5.1":{"pli":"… Bhaddā kāpilānī therī …. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p>"},"thig4.1:6.1":{"pli":"Catukkanipāto niṭṭhito. ","html":"<p class='endbook'>{}</p></article>"}},"thig5.1":{"thig5.1:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 5.1 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 5.1 ","html":"<article id='thig5.1'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig5.1:0.2":{"pli":"Pañcakanipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Fives ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig5.1:0.3":{"pli":"Aññataratherīgāthā ","eng":"An Unnamed Nun (2nd) ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig5.1:1.1":{"pli":"“Paṇṇavīsativassāni, ","eng":"In the twenty-five years ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig5.1:1.2":{"pli":"yato pabbajitā ahaṃ; ","eng":"since I went forth ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig5.1:1.3":{"pli":"Nāccharāsaṅghātamattampi, ","eng":"I have not found peace of mind, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig5.1:1.4":{"pli":"cittassūpasamajjhagaṃ. ","eng":"even for as long as a finger-snap. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig5.1:2.1":{"pli":"Aladdhā cetaso santiṃ, ","eng":"Failing to find peace of heart, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig5.1:2.2":{"pli":"kāmarāgenavassutā; ","eng":"festering with sensual desire, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig5.1:2.3":{"pli":"Bāhā paggayha kandantī, ","eng":"I cried with flailing arms ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig5.1:2.4":{"pli":"vihāraṃ pāvisiṃ ahaṃ. ","eng":"as I entered a dwelling. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig5.1:3.1":{"pli":"Sā bhikkhuniṃ upāgacchiṃ, ","eng":"I approached a nun ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig5.1:3.2":{"pli":"yā me saddhāyikā ahu; ","eng":"in whom I had faith. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig5.1:3.3":{"pli":"Sā me dhammamadesesi, ","eng":"She taught me the Dhamma: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig5.1:3.4":{"pli":"khandhāyatanadhātuyo. ","eng":"the aggregates, sense fields, and elements. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig5.1:4.1":{"pli":"Tassā dhammaṃ suṇitvāna, ","eng":"When I heard her teaching, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig5.1:4.2":{"pli":"ekamante upāvisiṃ; ","eng":"I retired to a discreet place. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig5.1:4.3":{"pli":"Pubbenivāsaṃ jānāmi, ","eng":"I know my past lives; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig5.1:4.4":{"pli":"dibbacakkhu visodhitaṃ. ","eng":"my clairvoyance is purified; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig5.1:5.1":{"pli":"Cetopariccañāṇañca, ","eng":"I encompass the minds of others; ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig5.1:5.2":{"pli":"sotadhātu visodhitā; ","eng":"my clairaudience is purified; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig5.1:5.3":{"pli":"Iddhīpi me sacchikatā, ","eng":"I’ve realized the psychic powers, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig5.1:5.4":{"pli":"patto me āsavakkhayo; ","eng":"and attained the ending of defilements. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig5.1:5.5":{"pli":"Chaḷabhiññā sacchikatā, ","eng":"I have realized the six kinds of direct knowledge, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig5.1:5.6":{"pli":"kataṃ buddhassa sāsanan”ti. ","eng":"and fulfilled the Buddha’s instructions. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig5.1:6.1":{"pli":"… Aññatarā therī …. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"thig5.10":{"thig5.10:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 5.10 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 5.10 ","html":"<article id='thig5.10'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig5.10:0.2":{"pli":"Pañcakanipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Fives ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig5.10:0.3":{"pli":"Paṭācārātherīgāthā ","eng":"Paṭācārā ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig5.10:1.1":{"pli":"“Naṅgalehi kasaṃ khettaṃ, ","eng":"Plowing the fields, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig5.10:1.2":{"pli":"bījāni pavapaṃ chamā; ","eng":"sowing seeds in the ground, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig5.10:1.3":{"pli":"Puttadārāni posentā, ","eng":"providing for partners and children, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig5.10:1.4":{"pli":"dhanaṃ vindanti māṇavā. ","eng":"young men acquire wealth. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig5.10:2.1":{"pli":"Kimahaṃ sīlasampannā, ","eng":"I am accomplished in ethics, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig5.10:2.2":{"pli":"satthusāsanakārikā; ","eng":"and I do the Teacher’s bidding, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig5.10:2.3":{"pli":"Nibbānaṃ nādhigacchāmi, ","eng":"being neither lazy nor restless—","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig5.10:2.4":{"pli":"akusītā anuddhatā. ","eng":"why then do I not achieve quenching? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig5.10:3.1":{"pli":"Pāde pakkhālayitvāna, ","eng":"Having washed my feet, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig5.10:3.2":{"pli":"udakesu karomahaṃ; ","eng":"I took note of the water, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig5.10:3.3":{"pli":"Pādodakañca disvāna, ","eng":"seeing the foot-washing water ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig5.10:3.4":{"pli":"thalato ninnamāgataṃ. ","eng":"flowing from high ground to low. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig5.10:4.1":{"pli":"Tato cittaṃ samādhesiṃ, ","eng":"My mind became serene, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig5.10:4.2":{"pli":"assaṃ bhadraṃvajāniyaṃ; ","eng":"like a fine thoroughbred steed. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig5.10:4.3":{"pli":"Tato dīpaṃ gahetvāna, ","eng":"Then, taking a lamp, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig5.10:4.4":{"pli":"vihāraṃ pāvisiṃ ahaṃ; ","eng":"I entered my dwelling, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig5.10:4.5":{"pli":"Seyyaṃ olokayitvāna, ","eng":"inspected the bed, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig5.10:4.6":{"pli":"mañcakamhi upāvisiṃ. ","eng":"and sat on my cot. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig5.10:5.1":{"pli":"Tato sūciṃ gahetvāna, ","eng":"Then, grabbing the pin, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig5.10:5.2":{"pli":"vaṭṭiṃ okassayāmahaṃ; ","eng":"I drew out the wick. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig5.10:5.3":{"pli":"Padīpasseva nibbānaṃ, ","eng":"The liberation of my heart ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig5.10:5.4":{"pli":"vimokkho ahu cetaso”ti. ","eng":"was like the quenching of the lamp. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig5.10:6.1":{"pli":"… Paṭācārā therī …. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}}}